parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering rack can cause a loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control, especially during low-speed turns.
symptoms: Audible clunking or popping noise while turning
excessive play in the steering mechanism
rattling noise and knocking of the steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the energy absorber shaft can cause excessive play in the steering mechanism, leading to a loss of steering control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: excessive play in the steering mechanism during low-speed turns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering knuckle can cause a loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Rattling noise and knocking of the steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical malfunction can cause a fire in the vehicle, potentially leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Smoke appears from the CD player
hot ignition switch and fob key.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat height adjuster mechanism can cause the driver's seat to become unattached or unstable, leading to a loss of control while driving, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The seat feels loose or unstable
the seat rocks back and forth
the seat moves up and down excessively
the seat becomes detached from the floor-mounted slides or brackets.
